  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "The formula is listed as follows:L self = - i∈I log exp h i • h j(i) /τ a∈A(i) exp (h i • h a /τ)(14)The contrastive loss encourages the similarity of positive pairs to be large enough (the numerator in formula 14) and encourages the similarity of negative pairs to be small enough (the denominator).",
    "Here, h i and h j(i) come from the same sample, with h i being called the anchor and h j(i) being called the positive instance.",
    "The symbol • generally is the dot product operation, the τ is a scalar temperature parameter and A(i) ≡ I \\{i}.",
    "Note that each anchor h i has one positive pair and 2N -2 negative pairs.",
    "Supervised Contrastive LossKhosla et al. [19] propose the supervised contrastive loss, which allows the model to leverage label information to split the positive and negative samples of an anchor and satisfy each anchor to have multiple positive samples."
  ],
